# invoice_mappings.example
#
# Maps client names (as they appear in receipt filenames) to invoice descriptions.
# Copy or adapt this file to wherever invoice_mappings_file points in your config.
#
# Format:  Client: Invoice description
#
# The client name must match exactly what appears in the receipt filename between
# the vendor and the .pdf extension:
#   "2026-03-16 Lowes - Birch.pdf"  →  client is "Birch"
#
# Lines starting with # are comments and are ignored.
# Blank lines are ignored.
#
# Each client should have at most one active entry — comment out old entries
# rather than deleting them so you keep a record.

# ── Active ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Birch: Invoice 0000348 - 43 Birch Rd
Appalachee: Invoice 0000351 - 89 Appalachee Rd
Wiscasset: Invoice 0000355 - 550 Wiscasset Rd

# ── Completed (keep for reference) ───────────────────────────────────────────

# Harbor: Invoice 0000312 - 14 Harbor View Ln
# Pine: Invoice 0000329 - 7 Pine St
